      <head>Heinrich Schenker</head>
      <div>
        <p>Austrian music theorist, editor, teacher, pianist, and composer. Leading 20th-century
          theorist of tonal music. The central figure of <hi rend="italic">Schenker Documents
            Online</hi>.</p>

        <p>For a detailed discussion of his life and work, go to <ref cRef="heinrich_schenker"
            >Heinrich Schenker</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <head>Artur Niloff</head>
        <p>Pseudonymous name for Heinrich Schenker, used as the author name for Schenker's <ref
            cRef="entity-001729"><title level="m">Instrumentationstabelle</title> (<title level="m"
              >Instrumentation Table</title>)</ref> (1908). </p>
      </div>
